       There are additional commands which are directly translated  to  python  functions,
       one  for  every  method  in  the  ranger.core.actions.Actions  class.  They are not
       documented here, since they are mostly for key bindings, not to be typed  in  by  a
       user.  Read the source if you are interested in them.

       These are the public commands including their descriptions:

       alias [[4mnewcommand[24m] [[4moldcommand[24m]
         Copies the oldcommand as newcommand.

       bulkrename
         This  command  opens  a  list of selected files in an external editor.  After you
         edit and save the file, it will generate a shell script which does bulk  renaming
         according to the changes you did in the file.

         This  shell script is opened in an editor for you to review.  After you close it,
         it will be executed.

       cd [[4mpath[24m]
         The cd command changes the directory.  If path is a file, selects that file.  The
         command ":cd -" is equivalent to typing ‘‘.

       chain [4mcommand1[24m[; [4mcommand2[24m[; [4mcommand3[24m...]]
         Combines multiple commands into one, separated by semicolons.

       chmod [4moctal_number[0m
         Sets the permissions of the selection to the octal number.

         The octal number is between 000 and 777. The digits specify the  permissions  for
         the  user, the group and others.  A 1 permits execution, a 2 permits writing, a 4
         permits reading.  Add those numbers to combine them. So a 7 permits everything.

         Key bindings in the  form  of  [-+]<who><what>  and  <octal>=  also  exist.   For
         example,  [1m+ar  [22mallows  reading for everyone, -ow forbids others to write and 777=
         allows everything.

         See also: man 1 chmod

       console [-p[4mN[24m] [4mcommand[0m
         Opens the console with the command already typed in.  The cursor is placed at [4mN[24m.

       copymap  [4mkey[24m [4mnewkey[24m [[4mnewkey2[24m ...]
       copycmap [4mkey[24m [4mnewkey[24m [[4mnewkey2[24m ...]
       copypmap [4mkey[24m [4mnewkey[24m [[4mnewkey2[24m ...]
       copytmap [4mkey[24m [4mnewkey[24m [[4mnewkey2[24m ...]
