         copy, so if you change the new binding (or parts of it) later, the old one is not
         modified.  For example, [4mcopymap[24m [4mj[24m [4mdown[24m will make the key sequence "down" move the
         cursor down one item.

         To copy key bindings of the console, pager or taskview use "copycmap", "copypmap"
         or "copytmap" respectively.

       default_linemode [[4mpath=regexp[24m | [4mtag=tags[24m] [4mlinemodename[0m
         Sets the default linemode.  See [4mlinemode[24m command.

